name: diesel cafe

comment: While they have delicious food and drink, unless you are setting up shop to work, they don't mind if you stop in to use the bathroom, and often are so busy it won't be noticeable. Come back sometime and buy something if you can't that day, or just pay the refuge forward somewhere. :)

name: Boards & Beans Cafe
directions: The bathrooms are around the corner from the ordering counter. The first one is wheelchair accessible, and the second bathroom has a baby changing table in it.
comment:
Since we have a 5 dollar cover charge for customers (to secure the working order of the board games we lend out) just let us know as you zip by the counter that you're only here to use the bathroom. You won't have to pay anything.

Also, there's a chalkboard wall in each of the bathrooms. You can absolutely draw or write something on them with the provided chalk as long as it's appropriate. :D

name: Delta Behavioral Health
directions: There is one single stall restroom in the back. Go through the doors on either side of the lobby and follow the hallway.
comment: They are a trans/gender nonconforming friendly mental heath and counseling clinic. They have never asked me whether or not I'm a patient omw to the reatroom. If they did, you could always say you're here to pick up a friend from a therapy session. It isn't officially handcapped accessible, but it is roomy and has handlebars on the wall by the toilet, plus a call button for if help is needed.

name: Delta Behavioral Health
